<p>The district-level data on area and intensity of salinity were collected from the Soil Resources Development Institute (SRDI). The salinity severity index was calculated using Equation (1): 
 <disp-formula id="FD1-ijerph-16-04552">
  <label>(1)</label>
  <math id="mm1">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>Salinity</mi>
      <mtext> </mtext>
      <mi>Severity</mi>
      <mtext> </mtext>
      <mi>Index</mi>
      <mtext> </mtext>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>SSI</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msubsup>
        <mstyle mathsize="70%" displaystyle="true">
         <mo>∑</mo>
        </mstyle>
        <mrow>
         <mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi>
         <mo>=</mo>
         <mn>0</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mn>5</mn>
       </msubsup>
       <msub>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">S</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mrow>
          <mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi>
          <mtext> </mtext>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <msub>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msubsup>
        <mstyle mathsize="70%" displaystyle="true">
         <mo>∑</mo>
        </mstyle>
        <mrow>
         <mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi>
         <mo>=</mo>
         <mn>0</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mn>5</mn>
       </msubsup>
       <msub>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">A</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where S
 <sub>i</sub> represents the salinity class; A
 <sub>i</sub> represents the % area under the i
 <sup>th</sup> salinity class, i.e., i = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5. S
 <sub>0</sub> = no salinity or &lt; 2 ds/m; S
 <sub>1</sub> = 2–4 ds/m; S
 <sub>2</sub> = 4–8 ds/m; S
 <sub>3</sub> = 8–12 ds/m; S
 <sub>4</sub> = 12–16 ds/m; S
 <sub>5</sub> = above 16 ds/m.
</p>
